{
  "texts": [
    "This configuration pertains specifically to the movement of two cylinders within the environment.",
    "Each integer corresponds to the movement direction of one cylinder, with the integers 0 through 7 representing distinct directions: north, east, west, south, northeast, northwest, southeast, and southwest, respectively.",
    "Consequently, each cylinder is capable of moving 1mm in the designated direction.",
    "For instance, a movement towards the north translates to a 1mm shift northwards, whereas a northwest movement entails a simultaneous 1mm displacement both north and west.1 self.action_space = spaces.MultiDiscrete( [7,7]))• Reward We use the same reward function as explained in Section 4.3.3.",
    "6DOF Case StudyIn this case study, we define the observation and action spaces to model the dynamics of a 6DOF robotic arm."
  ]
}